# 1. Project Overview

SkillFind.pro is a multilingual marketplace platform connecting clients with vetted professionals across categories such as coaching, tutoring, wellness, tech, creative, home services, and more.

Inspired by **Profi.ru**, the platform includes:

- Service request posting system  
- Offer responses from professionals  
- Pay-per-click professional billing  
- Profile verification system  
- Full admin panel  
- Multilingual support  
- Search and matching systems  
- Wallet and billing system  

---

# 2. Core Website Structure

## 2.1 Home Page
- Search bar (‚ÄúWhat do you need?‚Äù)
- Popular categories
- ‚ÄúHow it works‚Äù section
- Language selector dropdown

## 2.2 Category Pages
- Categories (e.g., Tutors, Coaches)
- Subcategories (e.g., English Tutors, Life Coaches)
- Filters: price, rating, location
- Featured professionals

## 2.3 Professional Profile Pages
- Name, photo, location
- Services offered
- Pricing (hourly or flat)
- Bio / Experience
- Reviews & Ratings
- Contact / ‚ÄúRequest Service‚Äù button

## 2.4 Client Dashboard
- Post service request
- View offers
- Manage communication
- Leave reviews

## 2.5 Professional Dashboard
- Profile setup
- Service management
- Incoming requests
- Messaging
- Wallet + billing history

## 2.6 Admin Panel
- User management
- Category + service management
- Content moderation
- Reports & analytics
- Advertising management

---

# 3. Multilingual Support

- Default: English  
- Auto-detect user location (via IP)  
- Auto-translate content using AI (ChatGPT 4o)  
- Manual language switcher  
- Use translation key system (i18n)  
- All text content must be stored as keys  

---

# 4. User Roles

1. **Client**  
2. **Professional**  
3. **Admin**

---

# 5. System Overview

Flow summary:

- Client submits a service request
- Verified professionals receive matching requests
- First 10 professionals may send offers
- When client clicks a pro‚Äôs offer ‚Üí **pro is charged ‚Ç¨0.10**
- If client chooses a pro ‚Üí both phone numbers revealed
- Service is completed offline

---

# 6. Client Flow

### Requirements:
- **+18 only**
- Registration with **phone & email verification**

## 6.1 Submit Request
Fields:
- Category, Subcategory  
- Description  
- Preferred time/days (optional)  
- Budget (optional)  
- Location or Online  

## 6.2 Receive Offers
Clients see:
- Message
- Proposed price/time
- Preview of rating & location

## 6.3 Click Offer ‚Üí triggers billing
- Opens full profile
- Pro is charged **‚Ç¨0.10**

## 6.4 Chat System
- Web chat between client and pro

## 6.5 Choose a Pro
- Phone numbers revealed to both sides  
- They finalize appointment privately

---

# 7. Professional Flow

### Requirements:
- **+18 only**
- Registration with phone + email verification

## 7.1 Mandatory Verification Steps  
(Count toward profile completion %)

| Step | Required | Notes |
|------|----------|--------|
| Email verification | ‚úî | Firebase |
| Phone verification | ‚úî | Firebase |
| Wallet connected | ‚úî | Stripe or PayPal (min ‚Ç¨2 balance) |
| ID Verification | ‚úî | iDenfy |
| Profile photo | ‚úî | Required |
| Bio filled | ‚úî | Required |
| Services selected | ‚úî | Minimum 1 |
| Remote availability | ‚úî | yes/no/only remote |
| Terms of use accepted | ‚úî | Required |

## Optional Uploads
- Diplomas, certificates  
- Project photos  

## Pro Profile Includes:
- Personal data (email, phone, location, bio)
- Services
- Completed projects
- Reviews
- Wallet & billing history

## 7.2 Receive Matching Requests
Pro dashboard displays all matching requests based on:
- Category  
- Subcategory  
- Location / Remote availability  

## 7.3 Send Offers
Includes:
- Price
- Time slots
- Custom message

## 7.4 Pay-Per-Click Billing
- When client views pro profile ‚Üí ‚Ç¨0.10 deducted  
- Daily budget limit (e.g., max 10 clicks)

## 7.5 Chat

## 7.6 If chosen
- Phone numbers revealed

---

# 8. Matching Logic

Matching based on:

- Category  
- Subcategory  
- City / region  
- Remote toggle  
- Verified tags  
- Service metadata  

---

# 9. Advertising System

Admin creates ad campaigns with:

- Target location  
- Category  
- Duration  
- Budget  
- Stats dashboard  

---

# 10. Ratings & Reviews System

## 10.1 Trigger Conditions
Review allowed only if:
- Client clicked ‚ÄúJob completed‚Äù
- Client was verified
- Job originated on SkillFind

## 10.2 Review Form
- 1‚Äì5 stars  
- Title (optional)  
- Feedback (min 30 chars)  
- Tags (optional)  
- ‚ÄúWould recommend‚Äù toggle  

## 10.3 Anti-spam
- One review per job  
- No anonymous reviews  
- Admin moderation required for flagged content  
- Pros may publicly reply  

---

# 11. Identity Verification (iDenfy)

- Mandatory for pro account activation  
- Verified badge: **‚ÄúVerified Professional‚Äù**  

---

# 12. Billing System (Professionals)

Integrations:
- Stripe  
- PayPal  

Features include:
- Wallet  
- Pay-per-click billing  
- Transaction logs  
- Daily limits  
- Balance top-up  

---

# 13. Search System (Elasticsearch)

Search by:
- Task  
- Service title  
- Keywords  
- Category  
- Location  
- Remote availability  

Supports:
- Typo tolerance  
- Partial match  
- Future: semantic search  

---

# 14. Content Moderation (Google Perspective API)

Moderates:
- Reviews  
- Bios  
- Descriptions  
- Optional: chat messages  

Filters for:
- Hate speech  
- Toxicity  
- Threats  
- Profanity

Threshold logic:
- Block highly toxic  
- Flag medium-risk for admin  

---

# 15. Email Notifications (SendGrid)

Used for:
- Welcome emails  
- Verification alerts  
- Review confirmations  
- Mass announcements  
- Automated system messages  

---

# 16. Admin Panel Requirements

## 16.1 User Management
### Professionals
- Filter by: verified/unverified, category, location, profile completion
- Actions: view/edit/delete, suspend, reverify, adjust balance

### Clients
- Filter by city/active  
- Actions: view requests, suspend/reactivate  

---

## 16.2 Content Moderation
### Reviews
- Flagged queue via Perspective API  
- Approve/reject/edit  
- Filter by category or rating  

### Bios & Descriptions
- Auto-flagged queue  
- Manual moderation  

### ID Verification
- Full iDenfy logs  
- Admin override  

---

## 16.3 Click & Wallet Tracking
- Pro wallet logs  
- Filters  
- Click history  
- Exportable CSV/PDF  

---

## 16.4 Request & Offer Management
- List all client requests  
- List all offers by professionals  
- Remove spam  
- Flag suspicious activity  

---

## 16.5 Services & Category Manager
- Add/edit/delete categories + subcategories  
- Tag groups  
- Display order
- Icons  
- Suggested services  

---

## 16.6 Advertising Management
- Create campaigns  
- Duration, budget, location, category  
- Generate Stripe payment links  
- Click statistics  

---

## 16.7 Platform Communications
- Mass emails via SendGrid  
- Triggered emails:
  - Welcome  
  - Suspension  
  - Verification failed  
  - Review received  

---

## 16.8 Analytics & Reports
- Daily signups  
- Daily requests  
- Booking trends  
- Most active categories  
- Export CSV/PDF  
- Optional Google Analytics  

---

## 16.9 Global Settings
- Per-click fee default: ‚Ç¨0.10  
- Minimum wallet threshold: ‚Ç¨2  
- Moderation thresholds  
- Chatbot fallback settings  

---

# 17. Support Chatbot (Chatbase)

Features:
- Guides users  
- Helps with registration, hiring, payment  
- Auto-adjusts language by IP/browser  
- Escalates complex issues to human support  

